severity of the infant's condition and the expectancy of cure. Thus, infants 
exhibiting acute symptoms of a disease may be more likely to be placed under the 
care of a 'western' type physician than taken for treatment to an indigenous 
medical practitioner. Such attitude on the part of the parents may, however, 
result in the loss of precious time at the most critical moments, and thus may 
reduce their chances of success to save their infant's life.(ABSTRACT TRUNCATED 
AT 250 WORDS)

