553. Med J Aust. 1985 Oct 28;143(SP9):S49-54. doi: 
10.5694/j.1326-5377.1985.tb120102.x.

An analysis of aboriginal mortality in NSW country regions, 1980-1981.

Thomson N, Smith L.

The total number of Aboriginal deaths occurring in selected country regions of 
New South Wales in 1980 and 1981 has been estimated, based on the deaths 
reported by Aboriginal health workers and those identified on the newly modified 
Form of Notification of Death. Aboriginal mortality was more than four times 
that of the total NSW population, with young and middle-aged adults having death 
rates up to 12 times higher. The Aboriginal expectation of life at birth was 
estimated at 48 years for men and 57 years for women. The principal causes of 
death were diseases of the circulatory system and injuries. The effect of 
alcohol appeared to be substantial, particularly in the 35-44 year age group.

